      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know it's not a miracle but i've read so much about medical grade honey being used in hospitals for skin wounds. it has antibacterial properties right? surely for a cut that isn't \"gaping\" open i could just clean it really well, put some honey on there to keep it moist, and wrap it tight? i'm just really trying to avoid the cost and the wait at the clinic if it's something i can manage myself.",
